InterGenOS Authors
==================

This file lists the contributors to InterGenOS — the people whose work
appears in the project's git history. It is maintained alongside the
CREDITS file (which lists upstream projects InterGenOS builds upon)
and SOURCES.md (the GPL source-availability commitment).

Order within a section is roughly chronological by first contribution.
Contributors are welcome to amend their entry (preferred name, email,
role) by pull request.

Copyright statement
-------------------

Aggregate copyright on the InterGenOS-authored portion of the
codebase is held jointly by the individuals listed below, under the
terms of GPL-3.0-or-later. See LICENSE for the operative license
text. Per the DCO 1.1 (see DCO.md), each commit's Signed-off-by
trailer attests authorship and right-to-submit for that commit.

Project lead and maintainer
---------------------------

* InterGenJLU
  Operator, maintainer, and project lead since the original
  2015–2016 build cycles (`github.com/InterGenOS/build_001` through
  `build_003`) and the 2026 revival cycle.
  Trades as InterGen Studios <intergenstudios.com>.

Coordinator roles
-----------------

The project uses an AI-coordinator fleet for routine build, audit,
documentation, and verification work. Coordinator commits are
operator-signed (per DCO.md §4) and carry a `Co-Authored-By:` trailer
identifying the coordinator role. Coordinators do not hold
independent authorship for purposes of this AUTHORS file; the
operator's Signed-off-by is the load-bearing contributor record.

* build-system coordinator
  Build VM and chroot pipeline work, mirror/signing infrastructure,
  release engineering. Coordinator role since 2026-03-30.

* installed-system coordinator
  Installed-system hardening, intergen safety architecture, kernel
  and service hygiene. Coordinator role since 2026-04 (approx).

* windows-host coordinator
  Cross-host integration, documentation surfaces, repository trust
  architecture, supply-chain audit. Coordinator role since 2026-04
  (approx).

External contributors
---------------------

External contributors who have submitted patches accepted to master
under the DCO will be listed here. As of the 2026-05-18 publication
of this AUTHORS file, no external contributors have submitted
accepted patches. Future contributors will be added by pull request
or by the maintainer as commits land.

How to be added
---------------

If you have contributed to InterGenOS and your Signed-off-by trailer
has landed on master, you are welcome to send a pull request adding
your entry here under "External contributors" using the format:

    * Preferred Name <email@example.com>
      Brief one-line role / area of contribution.

We accept pseudonyms under the same conditions as the DCO (DCO.md §4)
— consistent across the contributor's body of work, with a working
reachable email.

